	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001068_0001"/><!--pb/@n='68r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>London</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">Monday Morning </p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Murray</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I enclose in 
<lb/>one of these a 
<lb/>drawing of 
<lb/>the Marim-ba<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>I am going to 
<lb/>see <placeName>Windsor</placeName> today but return 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001068_0002"/><!--pb/@n='68v'--> 
<lb/>to <placeName>Hadley</placeName> this evening 
<lb/>I shall call on 
<lb/>my way back 
<lb/>if possible. 3 
<lb/>more will finish 
<lb/>the manuscript 
<lb/>one is nearly 
<lb/>finished. So 
<lb/>I will take 
<lb/>with me the 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001068_0003"/><!--pb/@n='69r'--> 
<lb/>copy. <choice><reg>T</reg><orig>t</orig></choice>hat which 
<lb/>I got is not 
<lb/>continuous<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>Please put up 
<lb/>all the pieces 
<lb/>with the corrections 
<lb/>previously made 
<lb/>and I will 
<lb/>give the final 
<lb/>touch as soon 
<lb/>as I finish the MSS<reg>.</reg></p>

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001068_0004"/><!--pb/@n='69v'-->
<lb/><p>I am &amp;c </p>
<lb/><p rend="center"><persName>D. Livingstone</persName></p>
			
